<template><div><h1 id="node-plop" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#node-plop" aria-hidden="true">#</a> Node-Plop</h1>
<p><a href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/node-plop" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/npm/v/node-plop.svg" alt="npm"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a>
<a href="https://github.com/plopjs/node-plop/actions/workflows/test.yml" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer"><img src="https://img.shields.io/github/workflow/status/plopjs/node-plop/test" alt="GitHub actions"><ExternalLinkIcon/></a></p>
<p>This is an early publication of the plop core logic being removed from the CLI tool. Main purpose for this is to make it easier for others to automate code generation through processes and tools OTHER than the command line. This also makes it easier to test the code functionality of PLOP without needing to test via the CLI interface.</p>
<p>This is the backend code that drives the plop CLI tool using node-plop.</p>
<div class="language-javascript ext-js line-numbers-mode"><pre v-pre class="language-javascript"><code><span class="token keyword">import</span> nodePlop <span class="token keyword">from</span> <span class="token string">'node-plop'</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">// load an instance of plop from a plopfile</span>
<span class="token keyword">const</span> plop <span class="token operator">=</span> <span class="token keyword">await</span> <span class="token function">nodePlop</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token template-string"><span class="token template-punctuation string">`</span><span class="token string">./path/to/plopfile.js</span><span class="token template-punctuation string">`</span></span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
<span class="token comment">// get a generator by name</span>
<span class="token keyword">const</span> basicAdd <span class="token operator">=</span> plop<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">getGenerator</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token string">'basic-add'</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>

<span class="token comment">// run all the generator actions using the data specified</span>
basicAdd<span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">runActions</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token punctuation">{</span><span class="token literal-property property">name</span><span class="token operator">:</span> <span class="token string">'this is a test'</span><span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">.</span><span class="token function">then</span><span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token keyword">function</span> <span class="token punctuation">(</span><span class="token parameter">results</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span> <span class="token punctuation">{</span>
  <span class="token comment">// do something after the actions have run</span>
<span class="token punctuation">}</span><span class="token punctuation">)</span><span class="token punctuation">;</span>
</code></pre><div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div></div></template>
